  "texts": [
    "This dual nature, the next section of the paper contends, also reflects in the peculiar ways in which interactions with artificial agents must-and must not-be transparent.",
    "So far, the sui generis character of affective artificial agents has been explored by focusing on their agency and their relationship with our sense of self.",
    "In this final section, we wish to draw attention to another feature that makes them significantly different from other affective artifacts.",
    "In particular, we will argue that, when it comes to affective artificial agents, a tension emerges between different kinds of transparency desiderata that has no immediate analogue in other affective artifacts.",
    "To give a bit of context, the notion of transparency has been playing a central role in the debate on artifacts within the philosophy of mind (e.g., Clark 2003; Heersmink 2015; Andrada 2020; Piredda and Di Francesco, 2020; Andrada et al. 2022; Smart et al. 2022; Facchin 2022)."
  ]
}